FBIS4-40547 "drsov117_a_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-117 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS World Bank Grants $320 Million for Agriculture World Bank Grants $320 Million for Agriculture LD1706020094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0005 GMT 17 Jun 94 LD1706020094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Borisenko] [Text] Washington, 17 June -- On Thursday the World Bank approved the granting of two loans to the Russian Federation for the development of agriculture. One of them -- for $240 million -- is intended for accelerating the process of reforms in the agricultural sector, for creating a network of information and consultation services for farmers, for help in organizing individual, highly efficient enterprises. The other -- for 80 million dollars -- should assist in the process of land reform and privatization. The loans are being granted on what are customary conditions for the World Bank, the repayment term is 17 years.
